TextBlock.TextLine: Gent francois Herrebout
In Antwerp 3 mars
Mons. in antwoort vanden ul van gisteren sal mijn rek verwaght
benten ujtterste verwondert dat pack A N36 gisteren noch niet
bij ul was nae demael de t coots schrijft dat p deser costij soude ween
Ick ben daer seer om verlegen soo dat niet magh versuynt worden om
p wagens te senden als mede de 2 stoffen packen wat passeert gelieft
aenstonts te laten weten waer pmedt blijve
In Antwepen 8 meert
Brugge
Raphael Coots
H in antwoort vande ul 26 & 28 pass. t gisteren hebbe advies van
8 Herrebout als wanneer N36 & andere 2 daer noch niet waeron
waerover mij niet alleen verwondere maer oock seer vllegen ben
want het selve is op de staelen verkoght & door het lanck tardeerende
vrinden met nae waghten wille, het pack AA.V.N. 23 was mede
noch niet tot gent over sulx soo noch costij is doet het pr bargie
voort gaen, met ordre tot gent 1 wagens herrewaerts te senden oft
van costij p wagen directelijck want daer mede haestigh om ben
godt verleene den melson & andere haest te arriveeren ofte anders
coopman sonder goedt sal wesen, degementioneerde bayen onder
de ƒ20: te verclaren costij mij de meest menighte 35 „ 30 a 38 s kcoste
oversulx daer geene risto in een rekene eghter kan ul sa
sommigh costen maer 32s nochtans kan ul daer van 40 stuck
van 30 tot 40 p weirde verclaren & de reft onder ƒ20 a governe
voor den brieff van £200: weet ul gecreditteert ter wijlen blijve
Brussel Andries Artsens
In Antwerpen 3 meert
Mons. mijnen vrint Peer booms is te rugge gekomen sonder ul eenigh
gelt betaelt te hebben, soo hebbe dan heden dese occasie waer genomen
ul te remitteeren tot laste gisberto vanden bist heuvel £100: onsich
den welke ul gelieft te doen accepteeren & vervolgens de betalinge
doen in voorderen, soo morgen de olst kan vinden sal ul remitteeren
soo met ul ordre moeten afraghten terwijlen vanden
ontfanck geirne ul advies bekomen & blijve
London Henry Maynard
In Antwerpen 4 march
S. my last to you was on the first curitt with a remise for £250: att 8
light on Richd ffoot & adesire to pay out of that £80: to in Icole
& £40 to mr. scuwen which is £150, so that remaines £130 for yd
acctt. thought I made bold to charge you with adraught for my acctt att
2 uso for £118„ 18„11: which is altered & is £521„ 14y 2 payable to mr.
Jean de la chambre for the valew of m. Hen: Van horenbeck, which
I hope you will accept, & redraw when dew, thought I do exspect to
prevent itt by remises, in order where unto Ill do all I can as well
for yd as my acctt. I should not have troubled you as above butt I could
finde No sundry bills, & because I took the £250: hadd itt for 35:7
where as I should have been obliged to allow 35:8½ att least to exspect
you will not take itt ill: in writing here off receave yd of 14 pas
with in voyce of a pack of bayes & spanishes cloathes aboard
Adriaen block for my halfe in which shall give you creditt, god
send him well over, as also lo dowich devos of which hve nomews
yett as soone you have the in voyce opattarnes of the goods
shipt, or ready in the north, please to send mee to governe my self
accordingly you will do well to provide the spenish cloathes
as desired and assort to directions I supose by this time that there
l
are ships enought arrived to come for Bruges, so that you can have
the opportunitie to divertrisico & haveyd owne time to provide good
& curlous goods & if any new mode coudes out, or acloth toy to yds
fancy, to add itt for our assortement towards Aprill & m'ay
I observe yd complaints of last yeares sale, I hope you will finde the
proffitt 10 ptV the ex. rekoned as I remitt, whoever itt is to be considdere
as you say all I can say is most of the extranagant charges which least
yeare were butt up on the goods, without not ce, or any miblick
declaration, so that most our goods suffered there by & I made the
calculation, after the formar rate because coots sended the acctt
of charges well 3 monthes after those new tares were come out
neither did he give the least notice there of by times to mee & thought
Iendeavoured after wards to advance accordingly, yett the extranagan
charges butts drawne downe part off proffitt, the complaints of
which is so furs claimed about, that, sence fer last the dut yes are
much diminished besides are order come out, that no goods shall be
more charges hence for ward with any other dutye, except that 6 month
before shall be given warning, for itt hath not been onely so imour
gooods butt up on fundry other com. wherfore recon the charges will
be about 3 a 3½ Pcen. less then formerly, besides wee had a good quancitio
of resting goods 1679 ub. x principally northrens of which I made
often complaints, so them are sold without great proffitt & after
a neare examination finde the acctt of resting goods made when I was
with you was overrated, I made itt £1245: & was not much above
£1200: besides the acctt. of resting goods made up last to be £1473„ 8„ 8 is
al most undervasved itt beeng the least penny they cost & by them you
will finde good gaine, so that in case you didexmin the goods in
perticular which you sent, sence I was in England, you well finde the
proffitt on them reasonable, whoever our wharenouse is clared of the
northren goods bj which wee had no proffijtt, & now wee have good resting
goods, which & most part is sold sence to noless then 12 bod. proffijt so
can desire you to keep the valuetion of £1473„8:8 in beeng & oddto
that the bale M„N 86 & what hece forward you shall send till mid
summer when I shall give you aiust & full accompt againe, & in cas
you finde not the praffitt then execeding 12 pr. shall be contented
to have goods up on my owne acctt. thought you are free to do so as you
please from now off, yett for yd owne advantidge itt will be as
well to continew till then my next shall without faile bring you
the acctt. of sale of Janu & fed last, which you may examin de
peruse against goods sold last yeare of the same prijses & in case you
are not in corridged, freely advise mee yd pleasure, besides lett mee
know how much you would rekon for buying & en suring to this
side, as also for goods from the north, besides what time you might
draw otme att the time will allow to have yd mony affer the day
of shipping or buying the goods, thatthen you have yd mony either
remitted or you might draw on mee att the time of expration, th
you allow for you must note I will by no meanes come to consent
any intrest pprincipally . P p annum, which Jean have hereatt
any time att 3 a 3½ p: where fore if wee concende the restishall
a lwayes make shist to be punituall in my payement, sothough I promise to
performe yd order yett lett you dispose of articles as you please &you will
finde mee willing to comply to keep a trade either onmy owne or incomp
so Remaine shall remitt mose p first
